Section 1:
1 L.D. 624
2 Date: (Filing No. H- )
3 STATE AND LOCAL GOVERNMENT
5 STATE OF MAINE
6 HOUSE OF REPRESENTATIVES
7 132ND LEGISLATURE
8 FIRST SPECIAL SESSION
9 COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 392, L.D. 624, “Resolve, to Create the
10 Commission to Study a Legislative Internship Program”
11 Amend the resolve in section 2 in the 2nd line (page 1, line 5 in L.D.) by striking out
12 the following: "12" and inserting the following: '10'
13 Amend the resolve in section 2 by striking out all of subsections 3 and 4 (page 1, lines
14 13 to 16 in L.D.).
15 Amend the resolve in section 2 by renumbering the subsections to read consecutively.
16 Amend the resolve in section 7 in the 2nd line (page 2, line 24 in L.D.) by striking out
17 the following: "February 1, 2026" and inserting the following: 'December 3, 2025'
18 Amend the resolve by inserting after section 7 the following:
19 'Sec. 8. Outside funding. Resolved: That the commission shall seek funding
20 contributions to fully fund the costs of the study. All funding is subject to approval by the
21 Legislative Council in accordance with its policies. If sufficient contributions to fund the
22 study have not been received within 30 days after the effective date of this resolve, no
23 meetings are authorized and no expenses of any kind may be incurred or reimbursed.'
24 Amend the resolve by relettering or renumbering any nonconsecutive Part letter or
25 section number to read consecutively.
26 SUMMARY
2277 This amendment, which is the majority report of the committee, removes the Executive
2288 Director of the Legislative Council, or the executive director's designee, as well as one
2299 member of the Executive Director of the Legislative Council's staff with responsibility for
3300 human resources matters from the membership of the Commission to Study a Legislative
3311 Internship Program. The amendment also changes the report submission deadline to
Page 1 - 132LR1908(02)
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT
COMMITTEE AMENDMENT “ ” to H.P. 392, L.D. 624
312 December 3, 2025 from February 1, 2026 and adds an additional section to the bill requiring
323 that the commission seek outside funding contributions to fully fund the cost of the study.
334 FISCAL NOTE REQUIRED
345 (See attached)
